<paragraph id="8B8F3696FFEF762030E5FCADB90F5339" blockId="9.[174,547,823,850]" box="[174,547,823,850]" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">
<heading id="D0C781FAFFEF762030E5FCADB90F5339" box="[174,547,823,850]" fontSize="36" level="2" pageId="9" pageNumber="20" reason="3">
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFEF762030E5FCADB90F5339" authority="Walker, 1839" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1839" box="[174,547,823,850]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Melittobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acasta">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFEF762030E5FCADBAAC5339" bold="true" box="[174,384,823,850]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">Melittobia acasta</emphasis>
Walker, 1839
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32A651DFFEF762030A8FCEDB97B5479" pageId="9" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8F3696FFEF762030A8FCEDBF3053D9" blockId="9.[174,1232,887,1042]" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFEF762030A8FCEDBA8753F9" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1839" box="[227,427,887,913]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Melittobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acasta">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFEF762030A8FCEDBA8753F9" box="[227,427,887,913]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">Melittobia acasta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
overtook 7.7 % of 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFEF762032CEFCE2B80F53F9" baseAuthorityName="Dahlbom" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[645,803,887,913]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Psenulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFEF762032CEFCE2B80F53F9" box="[645,803,887,913]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">P. fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cells and the pressure exerted on the host population is less considerable than the one exerted by 
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFEF76203325FC02BF3053D9" box="[878,1052,919,946]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFEF76203325FC02BF3453D9" authorityName=": Abeille de Perrin" authorityYear="1878" box="[878,1048,919,946]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera" genus="Omalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sculpticollis">O. sculpticollis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8F3696FFEF762030A8FC22B97B5479" blockId="9.[174,1232,887,1042]" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFEF762030A8FC22BA7D53B9" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1839" box="[227,337,952,977]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Melittobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acasta">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFEF762030A8FC22BA7D53B9" box="[227,337,952,977]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">M. acasta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
attacked also 14 cells (15.9 %) containing 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFEF76203366FC22B8FE53B9" authorityName=": Abeille de Perrin" authorityYear="1878" box="[813,978,951,978]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera" genus="Omalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sculpticollis">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFEF76203366FC22B8FE53B9" box="[813,978,951,978]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">O. sculpticollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
larvae. Consequently, 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFEF762030E5FC42BA325399" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1839" box="[174,286,984,1009]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Melittobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acasta">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFEF762030E5FC42BA325399" box="[174,286,984,1009]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">M. acasta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appeared to be parasitoid and hyperparasitoid at the same time for 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFEF76203478FC42BFFC5399" baseAuthorityName="Dahlbom" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[1075,1232,983,1009]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Psenulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFEF76203478FC42BFFC5399" box="[1075,1232,983,1009]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">P. fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C304D15FFEF762030AAFC62BAA45479" authorityName=": Abeille de Perrin" authorityYear="1878" box="[225,392,1015,1042]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera" genus="Omalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sculpticollis">
<emphasis id="B944EA84FFEF762030AAFC62BAA45479" box="[225,392,1015,1042]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="20">O. sculpticollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
correspondingly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
